Pereopods . Pereopods 3 and 4 absent. Pereopods 5–7 increasing in length, scarcely setose; basis with a distal triangular projection; basis of pereopods 6 and 7 with small granules on dorsal margin; merus with a rounded projection and some setae; carpus subrectangular, nearly as long as merus, with setae at dorsal and ventral margins; propodus provided with a pair of grasping spines proximally; dactylus curved (
Fig. 6
).
